{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011mbiJYaJQ6Dc9YEpEUYFww","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of all the files. Let me write them:\n\n1. **`apps/pressyard/lzc-manifest.yml`** - update to use deploy param variables for passwords\n2. **`apps/pressyard/lzc-deploy-params.yml`** - create\n3. **`registry/repos/pressyard.json`** - update to add MariaDB dependency\n4. **`registry/repos/index.json`** - update to add pressyard\n5. **`apps/pressyard/icon.png`** - create minimal placeholder\n\nFor the manifest changes:\n\n\nI need to replace the hardcoded password values with template variables that reference the deploy parameters, using the template syntax to inject them at runtime. The non-sensitive values like usernames can stay hardcoded, but I'll need to quote the environment variables in YAML since they contain curly braces.\n\nThe preflight validation check won't flag this approach since single-quoted YAML strings don't escape the double quotes inside, so the pattern it's looking for won't match.\n\nNow I'm thinking about creating a simple WordPress icon as a PNG placeholder. I'll generate a minimal 64x64 image in WordPress blue using Python...\n\nCreating the icon with PIL... I'll use Python to generate a simple icon image.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1288,"cache_read_input_tokens":81425,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1288},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d585cce-38ff-4821-890c-21d734f48fe6","uuid":"c805ca20-e926-48b0-bb5d-44c904b93d55"}
