{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCcpS3Jnw5ozHhcLMc6DKS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tlzc-sdk-version: '0.1'\n2\tpackage: fun.selfstudio.app.migration.pressyard\n3\tversion: 1.5.0\n4\tname: PressYard\n5\tdescription: Local WordPress development environment with isolated containers, automatic installs, and project-based hostnames.\n6\tlicense: UNLICENSED\n7\thomepage: https://github.com/CodeMasters999/PressYard\n8\tauthor: CodeMasters999\n9\tapplication:\n10\t  subdomain: pressyard\n11\t  upstreams:\n12\t    - location: /\n13\t      backend: http://wordpress:80/\n14\t  injects:\n15\t    - builtin://simple-inject-password\n16\tlocales:\n17\t  en:\n18\t    name: PressYard\n19\t    description: Local WordPress development environment with isolated containers, automatic installs, and project-based hostnames.\n20\t  zh:\n21\t    name: PressYard\n22\t    description: 使用隔离容器创建本地 WordPress 开发环境，支持自动安装与基于项目的主机名管理。\n23\tservices:\n24\t  wordpress:\n25\t    image: registry.lazycat.cloud/codemasters999/pressyard:wordpress\n26\t    depends_on:\n27\t      - db\n28\t    environment:\n29\t      - WORDPRESS_DB_HOST=db:3306\n30\t      - WORDPRESS_DB_USER=wordpress\n31\t      - 'WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD={{ index .U \"db_password\" }}'\n32\t      - WORDPRESS_DB_NAME=wordpress\n33\t    binds:\n34\t      - /lzcapp/var/data/pressyard/wp-content:/var/www/html/wp-content\n35\t    healthcheck:\n36\t      test:\n37\t        - CMD-SHELL\n38\t        - curl -fs http://127.0.0.1:80/ >/dev/null || exit 1\n39\t      interval: 30s\n40\t      timeout: 10s\n41\t      retries: 5\n42\t  db:\n43\t    image: registry.lazycat.cloud/codemasters999/pressyard:db\n44\t    environment:\n45\t      - MYSQL_DATABASE=wordpress\n46\t      - MYSQL_USER=wordpress\n47\t      - 'MYSQL_PASSWORD={{ index .U \"db_password\" }}'\n48\t      - 'MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD={{ index .U \"db_root_password\" }}'\n49\t    binds:\n50\t      - /lzcapp/var/db/pressyard/mysql:/var/lib/mysql\n51\t    healthcheck:\n52\t      test:\n53\t        - CMD-SHELL\n54\t        - mysqladmin ping -h 127.0.0.1 -u root -p$$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD --silent\n55\t      interval: 10s\n56\t      timeout: 5s\n57\t      retries: 10\n58\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d585cce-38ff-4821-890c-21d734f48fe6","uuid":"77a140a4-ef4f-4d18-9950-82bff93d23f4","timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:35:04.852Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/__w/lzcat-apps/lzcat-apps/apps/pressyard/lzc-manifest.yml","content":"lzc-sdk-version: '0.1'\npackage: fun.selfstudio.app.migration.pressyard\nversion: 1.5.0\nname: PressYard\ndescription: Local WordPress development environment with isolated containers, automatic installs, and project-based hostnames.\nlicense: UNLICENSED\nhomepage: https://github.com/CodeMasters999/PressYard\nauthor: CodeMasters999\napplication:\n  subdomain: pressyard\n  upstreams:\n    - location: /\n      backend: http://wordpress:80/\n  injects:\n    - builtin://simple-inject-password\nlocales:\n  en:\n    name: PressYard\n    description: Local WordPress development environment with isolated containers, automatic installs, and project-based hostnames.\n  zh:\n    name: PressYard\n    description: 使用隔离容器创建本地 WordPress 开发环境，支持自动安装与基于项目的主机名管理。\nservices:\n  wordpress:\n    image: registry.lazycat.cloud/codemasters999/pressyard:wordpress\n    depends_on:\n      - db\n    environment:\n      - WORDPRESS_DB_HOST=db:3306\n      - WORDPRESS_DB_USER=wordpress\n      - 'WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD={{ index .U \"db_password\" }}'\n      - WORDPRESS_DB_NAME=wordpress\n    binds:\n      - /lzcapp/var/data/pressyard/wp-content:/var/www/html/wp-content\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD-SHELL\n        - curl -fs http://127.0.0.1:80/ >/dev/null || exit 1\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 5\n  db:\n    image: registry.lazycat.cloud/codemasters999/pressyard:db\n    environment:\n      - MYSQL_DATABASE=wordpress\n      - MYSQL_USER=wordpress\n      - 'MYSQL_PASSWORD={{ index .U \"db_password\" }}'\n      - 'MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD={{ index .U \"db_root_password\" }}'\n    binds:\n      - /lzcapp/var/db/pressyard/mysql:/var/lib/mysql\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD-SHELL\n        - mysqladmin ping -h 127.0.0.1 -u root -p$$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD --silent\n      interval: 10s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 10\n","numLines":58,"startLine":1,"totalLines":58}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TCTDDKR7KQ6RieTNhRmn8r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The manifest looks good. Now let me verify all files are properly set.\n\nBut wait - there's still one issue: the `db` service's MariaDB `healthcheck` uses `$$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD` which references the env var inside the container. But since the env var is now a template `{{ index .U \"db_root_password\" }}`, the container will have it as an actual password value at runtime, so `$$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD` will work correctly (the YAML `$$` escapes to a literal `$` in the compose specification).\n\n\nActually, let me reconsider the escaping here. The `$$` in the YAML healthcheck command becomes a single `$` in the shell, so `$$MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD` resolves to the actual password value that MariaDB has set as an environment variable at runtime - this is correct.\n\nNow I need to verify the `builtin://simple-inject-password` inject has the right deploy params defined, which it does with `login_user` and `login_password`. But I should check if WordPress needs the login URL adjusted to `/wp-login.php` instead of the root path.\n\nActually, there's a potential issue: on first access, WordPress redirects to the setup wizard at `/wp-admin/install.php` rather than the login page, so the password injection won't trigger initially. That said, this limitation is acceptable given the `waiting_for_human` state already documents this behavior.\n\nI'm also verifying that `WORDPRESS_DB_USER` and `MYSQL_USER` are both set to `wordpress` consistently across services, which is fine since it's not a sensitive value. Now let me check the `depends_on` relationship to ensure the WordPress service waits for the database to be ready.\n\nLooking at the queue item more closely, I see the state is `build_failed` with `migration_status: waiting_for_human`, and while I can't modify the queue directly since it's orchestrator-managed, the `migration_status` in the registry config is the appropriate place to signal this.\n\nThe core issue is that there's no LICENSE file, which should trigger a `waiting_for_human` state. When I exit, the orchestrator will use my outputs to determine whether to mark this as `waiting_for_human` or attempt another build. Since the task asks me to surface blockers through the manifest, Dockerfile template, or queue field, and I can't edit the queue directly, the signal needs to come from the registry configuration I'm setting up.\n\nThe registry config already has `migration_status: waiting_for_human` set, and the README clearly documents the blockers. I should ensure my output summary reinforces this state so the orchestrator knows not to proceed with the build.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":847,"cache_read_input_tokens":85594,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":847},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d585cce-38ff-4821-890c-21d734f48fe6","uuid":"f20c824f-1be8-4985-97ba-622dfeb79349"}
