{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DYEAcfYjhwUtiqu76mfvxY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All files are in place. Here's my planning summary:\n\n---\n\n**PLANNER: waiting_for_human — scaffold updated**\n\n**Build strategy chosen:** `official_image`\n\n- Main service (`wordpress`): copies `docker.io/library/wordpress:latest` to LazyCat registry via `official_image_registry`\n- DB service (`db`): copies `docker.io/library/mariadb:10.11` via `dependencies[0].source_image`\n\n**Files written / modified:**\n\n| File | Action | Key change |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/pressyard/lzc-manifest.yml` | Updated | Replaced hardcoded `wordpress_secret` / `root_secret` with `{{ index .U \"db_password\" }}` / `{{ index .U \"db_root_password\" }}` deploy-param templates |\n| `apps/pressyard/lzc-deploy-params.yml` | Created | Defines `login_user`, `login_password` (secret, `$random(len=20)`), `db_password`, `db_root_password` |\n| `apps/pressyard/icon.png` | Created | 64×64 placeholder PNG (WordPress blue) — must be replaced before store submission |\n| `registry/repos/pressyard.json` | Updated | Added MariaDB `dependencies` entry; added `official_image_fallback_tag: latest` |\n| `registry/repos/index.json` | Updated | Added `\"pressyard\"` — was an empty array, would have caused build-chain failure |\n\n**Key decisions:**\n\n- **Ports**: WordPress on container port 80, proxied via LazyCat reverse proxy at `/`\n- **Login route**: `builtin://simple-inject-password` with `login_user` / `login_password` deploy params. WordPress login is at `/wp-login.php`; first run redirects to `/wp-admin/install.php` (setup wizard) — passwordless inject only activates after the user completes the wizard using the displayed deploy-param credentials\n- **Data paths**: `wp-content` → `/lzcapp/var/data/pressyard/wp-content`, MariaDB data → `/lzcapp/var/db/pressyard/mysql`\n- **Credentials**: All secrets parametrised with `$random(len=20)` defaults; consistent between `wordpress` and `db` services via shared `db_password` deploy param\n\n**Blockers flagged (waiting_for_human):**\n\n1. **No LICENSE file** — upstream `CodeMasters999/PressYard` has no LICENSE. Legal risk unquantified. A human must decide whether to proceed.\n2. **Tool vs. service mismatch** — PressYard is a local-dev tool that orchestrates multi-project WordPress environments via Traefik + custom hostnames. This migration deploys a single-project WordPress instance; the multi-project management UI is absent. Human must confirm this scope reduction is acceptable.\n3. **Passwordless login limitation** — official WordPress image has no WP-CLI; `login_user` / `login_password` deploy params cannot auto-configure the admin account. First-run setup wizard is manual. To enable true auto-setup, switch `build_strategy` to `target_repo_dockerfile` and add a Dockerfile that installs WP-CLI.\n4. `enabled: false` and `migration_status: waiting_for_human` are set in `registry/repos/pressyard.json` — build pipeline will not run until a human unblocks."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2132,"cache_read_input_tokens":86441,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2132},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d585cce-38ff-4821-890c-21d734f48fe6","uuid":"730b2b6c-7a9c-4227-9456-71b3304b08b8"}
